      <h3>To update your profile information</h3>
      <p>Your public profile shows the software you've entered in hackathon and personal information that you may have entered upon sign-up, such as your photo, location, bio, Twitter handle, website, or skills.</p>

      <p><em>Please note: we will never make your email address or full name public. For more information on what will be shown to the public, please see our privacy policy</em>.</p>

      <ol>
        <li>Log in to your Devpost account.</li>
        <li>Click your username at the top right corner of the page.</li>
        <li>From the dropdown menu, select "<strong>Settings</strong>."</li>
        <li>Select "<strong>Info</strong>" to edit your photo, name, location, bio, Twitter handle, or website. Click "<strong>Save Changes</strong>" after you’ve updated your information.</li>
      </ol>

      <p><a href="index.html">← Return to Devpost Support Center</a></p>
